Verification contract (from §D.2 verify block):
  ✓ all endpoints covered with auth + invalid-body cases
  ✓ create → GET (matches) → PUT (version 2 + snapshot row) → DELETE (archived_at) → GET 404 — sequence runs end-to-end live

Notes / minor design choices:
  - DELETE on already-archived returns 200 + {idempotent: true} (not 404).
    Spec only requires "GET-after-delete returns 404"; idempotent
    semantics are operator-friendly.
  - POST emits an INITIAL v1 snapshot at creation (beyond spec). This
    means the v1 snapshot exists from day one; the PUT-time snapshot is
    a no-op-via-ON-CONFLICT for the original v1 record but kicks in for
    subsequent PUTs (v2→v3 etc).
  - JSONB writes use `${JSON.stringify(value)}::jsonb` matching the
    cloud-runs.ts / approvals.ts pattern. The drizzle MCP/postgres-js
    parse-once cast is correct here (different from worker's sql.json
    helper which is for postgres-js direct).
